data.meta_site_name: Association of State Floodplain Managers | ASFPM’s mission is to promote education, policies and activities that mitigate current and future losses, costs and human suffering caused by flooding.
data.text:
Participation in the Certified Floodplain Manager Program (CFM® Program) is strictly voluntary. The program is designed to establish educational, training, and experience criteria related to floodplain management, hazard mitigation, and the National Flood Insurance Program, and to certify that an individual applicant has met these criteria.

The ASFPM assumes no liability for any action or inaction made by individual Certified Floodplain Managers (CFMs) during the course of performing their assigned duties and responsibilities. The ASFPM will not attempt to independently verify the information submitted by certification applicants. Further, the ASFPM assumes no liability or responsibility for any action or inaction made by an ASFPM accredited Chapter in accepting, denying, certifying, or renewing CFMs.

To protect the privacy of our members, ASFPM generally does not publish addresses, telephone numbers and email addresses on our website. If you would like to contact a CFM from this list or if you are a CFM and you do not see your name on this list, please email us.
